Description: Body sherd of possibly South Ionian pottery cup, possibly a cup with everted rim or a skyphos; interior: glazed black (fired red); exterior: glazed black (fired red); inscription on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Curator's comments: The fabric is close to that of 1965,0930.748-751, but far less micaceous.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 718, no. 761)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 114, NAU 75, pl.15p-q)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.752) (Phase 3)
